<subSubSection id="09B76511FF84FFABFF47EC9C2816CFD2" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="4112369AFF84FFABFF47EC9C2836CEE8" blockId="4.[173,659,1186,1233]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="61BD11B4FF84FFABFF47EC9C2836CEE8" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
<treatmentCitation id="C00C108BFF84FFABFF47EC9C28F6CE8E" author="Agathidium Panzer in North Zimmermann, C." box="[173,656,1186,1207]" page="250" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" year="1869">
<taxonomicName id="86AD4D19FF84FFABFF47EC9C28F6CE8E" authority="Zimmermann 1869: 250" authorityName="Zimmermann" authorityPageNumber="250" authorityYear="1869" box="[173,656,1186,1207]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Cyrtusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blandissima">
<emphasis id="73D9EA88FF84FFABFF47EC9C2B1BCE8E" box="[173,381,1186,1207]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Cyrtusa blandissima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="253C4B6BFF84FFABFE64EC9C28F6CE8E" author="Agathidium Panzer in North Zimmermann, C." box="[398,656,1186,1207]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 167" refId="ref6640" refString="beetles of the genus Agathidium Panzer in North Zimmermann, C. 1869. In: Synonymical notes on Co- and Central America, Part II. Coleoptera: Leiodi- leoptera of the United States, with descriptions of new dae. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural species, from MSS. of the late Dr. C. Zimmermann History 291: 1 - 167. (J. L. LeConte editor). Transactions of the" type="journal article" year="1869">Zimmermann 1869: 250</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
; misidentification by Matthews 1887: 85.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4112369AFF84FFABFF2FECD92816CFD2" blockId="4.[173,660,1255,1730]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
Matthews listed this species under the name 
<taxonomicName id="86AD4D19FF84FFABFF47ED3F2830CF2F" authority="Zimmermann, 1869" authorityName="Zimmermann" authorityYear="1869" box="[173,598,1281,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Cyrtusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blandissima">
<emphasis id="73D9EA88FF84FFABFF47ED3F2B1DCF2F" box="[173,379,1281,1302]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Cyrtusa blandissima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="253C4B6BFF84FFABFE61ED3F2830CF2F" author="Agathidium Panzer in North Zimmermann, C." box="[395,598,1281,1302]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 167" refId="ref6640" refString="beetles of the genus Agathidium Panzer in North Zimmermann, C. 1869. In: Synonymical notes on Co- and Central America, Part II. Coleoptera: Leiodi- leoptera of the United States, with descriptions of new dae. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural species, from MSS. of the late Dr. C. Zimmermann History 291: 1 - 167. (J. L. LeConte editor). Transactions of the" type="journal article" year="1869">Zimmermann, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This name, as applied by Matthews, was a misidentification, and the correctly identified name is now recognized as being a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="86AD4D19FF84FFABFDD0ED6F2807CFB8" authority="(Melsheimer, 1844) (Daffner 1989)" authorityName="Daffner" authorityYear="1989" baseAuthorityName="Melsheimer" baseAuthorityYear="1844" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Anogdus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoletus">
<emphasis id="73D9EA88FF84FFABFDD0ED6F2B68CFB8" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Anogdus obsoletus</emphasis>
(Melsheimer, 1844) (
<bibRefCitation id="253C4B6BFF84FFABFE32ED52283CCFB8" author="Daffner, H." box="[472,602,1388,1409]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" pagination="37 - 72" refId="ref6113" refString="Daffner, H. 1989. Revision der nordamerickanischen mologia 9: 37 - 72." type="journal article" year="1989">Daffner 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This species is distributed from 
<collectingRegion id="8369F878FF84FFABFE2CEDB82868CFA2" box="[454,526,1414,1435]" country="Canada" name="Ontario" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Ontario</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="8369F878FF84FFABFDA0EDB828F4CFA2" box="[586,658,1414,1435]" country="Canada" name="Quebec" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Québec</collectingRegion>
south to 
<collectingRegion id="8369F878FF84FFABFF17ED9F2B52CF8F" box="[253,308,1441,1462]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Texas</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="8369F878FF84FFABFE8AED9F2BD3CF8F" box="[352,437,1441,1462]" country="United States of America" name="Alabama" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Alabama</collectingRegion>
(Peck and Cook 2013). We therefore describe the single Guatemalan specimen cited by Matthews as a new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
